"{\"uid\": \"canadafreepress.com-article-vatican-issues-half-baked-response-to-olympics-blasphemy\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"David Martin--Bio and Archives--August 5, 2024  World News|CFP Comments|Reader Friendly|Subscribe|Email Us  The Vatican has finally broken the silence and voiced itsresponseto the Olympics' attack on the Last Supper on July 27.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Vatican Press Office issued the following over the weekend:  At a glance the statement appears to have an air of remorse, but there lies a hidden agenda.\", \"from\": 228, \"to\": 385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 232, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See_Press_Office\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vatican Press Office\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See_Press_Office\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See_Press_Office\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First of all, the Vatican does not identify the perpetrators behind this offense [ LGBT drag queens] nor does it cite the nature of the offense [blasphemous attack on the Last Supper].\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 469, \"end\": 473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"score\": 0.9953897550523712, \"rank\": 0.004500711386077962, \"text\": \"LGBT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why the silence?\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 587, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While admitting the event was wrong, Rome is exploiting it to suggest that we dignify other religions.\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 691, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"score\": 0.9043321671871478, \"rank\": 0.10578832468278304, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement emphasizes that we should not offend \\\"believers of other religions\\\" but fails to mention that the Olympics ceremony offended God.\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nor does it mention that the devotees of the Last Supper - the world's Catholics - were the ones targeted by this attack.\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 907, \"end\": 916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999993683559, \"rank\": 6.072645244008043e-10, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"*Other religions do not have devotion to the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 1015, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement continues:  Allusions?\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1053, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The attack on the Last Supper was a blatant, malicious, and deliberate commission of blasphemy against the Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1161, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999998581188, \"rank\": 1.1584827723664207e-10, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Where is the allusion?\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1200, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The intention was to mock the Church before the world.\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1255, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Why has this not been acknowledged in clear sound?\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And why has not Rome demanded that the International Olympic Committee apologize for this  public blasphemy?\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1324, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"score\": 0.9043321671871478, \"rank\": 0.10578832468278304, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\"}, {\"begin\": 1347, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The committee'sfake apologyof \\\"inclusion\\\" and \\\"diversity\\\" holds no water.\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1490, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Vatican statement added:  Not necessarily.\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1538, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If the expression is one of goodness and truth there are no limits, even if it offends the whole world.\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1642, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Catholic truth 'offends' most religions, so should we tone it down for them out of 'respect?'\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1643, \"end\": 1651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999995853828245, \"rank\": 4.143942915127959e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Romesupportsand is careful about not offending LGBT \\\"convictions\\\" but has no problem insulting Roman Catholic convictions.\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1784, \"end\": 1788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"score\": 0.9953897550523712, \"rank\": 0.004500711386077962, \"text\": \"LGBT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\"}, {\"begin\": 1832, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999731699, \"rank\": 2.667204566983117e-11, \"text\": \"Roman Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In short, the Vatican statement is an evasive, half-baked response to the Olympics' obscene attack on the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 1979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It does not decry this abomination that offended God and that made a laughingstock of His Church.\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 2077, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rome should at least admonish the satanic LGBT group that waged this attack, but Francis refuses to do this.\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2079, \"end\": 2083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"score\": 0.9043321671871478, \"rank\": 0.10578832468278304, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\"}, {\"begin\": 2121, \"end\": 2125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"score\": 0.9953897550523712, \"rank\": 0.004500711386077962, \"text\": \"LGBT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\"}, {\"begin\": 2160, \"end\": 2167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.827035917562317e-12, \"text\": \"Francis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is against the idea of correcting homosexuals.\", \"from\": 2188, \"to\": 2237, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He is quick to \\\"correct\\\" those who admonish them but willnever correctthe real offenders.\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This raises serious questions.\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"* We should not rule out that the perpetrators of this obscene \\\"Last Supper\\\" not only attempted to profane the Last Supper but were putting across the message that the Last Supper is what offends other religions.\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2573, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many religions indeed abhor the Last Supper and it could be that these interlopers were simply fueling this contempt by their weird, satanic parody.\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"View Comments  David Martin is the former moderator for St. Michaels Radio which is the one radio program of our time specializing in Catholic prophecy.\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2745, \"end\": 2751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.9999994270407846, \"rank\": 5.729021328411585e-07, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}, {\"begin\": 2858, \"end\": 2866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999995853828245, \"rank\": 4.143942915127959e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has also authored numerous articles on the Church and the Papacy which have appeared on various blogs and websites.\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 2995, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2938, \"end\": 2944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\", \"score\": 0.9872509154560255, \"rank\": 0.012913714464005976, \"text\": \"Papacy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"David presently resides in Los Angeles, California where for thirty years he has coordinated a Catholic ministry.\", \"from\": 2997, \"to\": 3110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3037, \"end\": 3047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999999969863893, \"rank\": 2.2596646257406665e-09, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}, {\"begin\": 3092, \"end\": 3100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999995853828245, \"rank\": 4.143942915127959e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is a daily communicant in his parish church and strongly supports Benedict XVI's aspiration to see the Traditional Latin Mass returned to every Catholic parish of the world.\", \"from\": 3111, \"to\": 3287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3180, \"end\": 3188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Benedict_XVI\", \"score\": 0.999999999953161, \"rank\": 4.693397218896815e-11, \"text\": \"Benedict\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Benedict_XVI\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Benedict_XVI\"}, {\"begin\": 3258, \"end\": 3266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999995853828245, \"rank\": 4.143942915127959e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Support Canada Free Press  Link, Bookmark, Share, Subscribe, Donate  Support Canada Free Press  Purs